@* Nested composition: the parent composes <Mid>, which itself composes <Grand>. Three levels
   deep, all inlined into one mount(); the reactive @V is threaded through each boundary and
   ends as a single live effect on the parent's signal. *@
<div id="w"><button id="g" @onclick="Go">g</button><Mid V="@x" /></div>

@code {
    private int x = 0;
    private void Go() { x++; }
}
